args:
Eventually, the prince and his friends reach a
giant landship owned by Chelle. In the name of
＂entertainment,＂ she plans to have Leif, the
royal family's battle instructor, fight fiends
near the ship. Seeing the danger his former
teacher is in, the prince sets out to rescue him.
...Wait, so this is it? We hit the X\non the map or whatever?
Maybe Jupiter's right and there's\na hidden oasis around somewhere.
Do you truly think an oasis could survive\nin a desolate hell such as this?
I agree that it seems unlikely to hold\nlife at first glance, Paladyn.
And yet, I see something approaching us;\nan object of quite incredible size.
Oh man, I can HEAR it comin'!
NOOOO! THE MOUNTAIN IS ALIIIIVE!\nIT'S GONNA EAT US AAAAAALL!
Hang on. That's not a mountain. It's...
It is a ship. ...On land.\nOf all the ridiculous things!
Yeah, this is a new one for me, too.
Methinks I hear the dulcet tones of my\nsweet brother's voice. Are you there,\n{player_name}?
In the flesh! I have come here\nspecifically to fetch you all.
The craft before you is the pride of the\nRadiant City—the landship Gran Fiore!

Vehicle? This is no mere conveyance—
it can ferry its distinguished passengers
across the desert in style and grace.
Why, it is a veritable mobile palace!

No expense was spared to lavish
it with every conceivable luxury—
including the finest banquet hall
in all the land.
And with that, I would like to formally\nwelcome all of you aboard.

Ladies and gentlemen, please rise and
join me in welcoming my brother—
seventh heir to the throne of Alberia—
and his royal retinue!
This landship truly is bedecked\nlike a royal court.
It has been quite some time,\nmy dear {player_name}.
I'm sorry for the long silence between us,\nChelle, but I'm glad you seem to be well.
I'm merely pleased you remember me.
Do you recall how we used to play\ngames of horsey when we were young?
This lady looks all fancy and junk,\nbut she ain't half-bad.
You really did make a fine horse,\n{player_name}.
You were quite comfortable—AND you\nobeyed any command given you!
Wait a sec. The horse was YOU?!
I, um... Well, I was little, and...\nYou know what? Let's just forget it.
So is your gala taking place\ninside this ship, Chelle?

Indeed. Now, I know you are weary from
the road, but we have stylish tuxedos and
elegant dresses in all sizes—so if you
would be so kind as to get changed?
It is a kind offer, but I must refuse.
It pleases me to see the prince and\nhis sister rekindling old ties.
However, given the terrible actions\ncurrently being undertaken by the Empire,\nI am not particularly given to levity.
My, but you are rather free\nwith your opinions, sylvan!
But let us see how disinclined\nto levity you truly are.
Attendants! Take the sylvan to the\ndressing room and let her have her pick!
Ho there, what are you doing?!\nUnhand me at once!
Goodness... I have never SEEN\nso many wonderful dresses...
Does levity still escape you, sylvan?\nIf so, I would have you prove it.
Choose the dress that suits you!\nAny dress at all!
I don't know that any of them suit me,\nbut if you insist...
Ah, this one is like something\nfrom a faerie tale...
Yes, I think this one is—
Oh no. That will not do at all.
What?! But that is the dress that I...\nBah. I knew this was a useless exercise.
Now, now—it is merely your method of\nselection that fails you, sylvan.

A person's clothing is a tool for presenting
themselves to the world. You are clearly
not of noble birth, so why would you
possibly pretend as such?
It seems I must be your chambermaid\nfor the day. Hmm... Perhaps...
Ah, yes! This is PERFECT for you, sylvan!\nThis dress will make for a glorious debut!
Hot damn, Cleo! Look at you!
It is not an outfit I would have envisioned\non you, and yet it simply screams ＂Cleo.＂
Behold the impassioned gazes\ndirected your way, sylvan!

Commoners have their own style of beauty.
And nothing is more arresting than
embracing one's natural aesthetics!
Eee hee hee!
Enough! Save your honeyed words!\nI am in no mood for frivolity!

Eee hee hee! And yet your eyes tell me
that you are not wholly displeased!
Come now—surely you must be feeling
at least SOME levity at the moment.
My, but you ARE a stubborn one.\nWell then, if the romance of wearing\na gorgeous frock is not enough...
Ah, what perfect timing. A prince arrives!
Would you be so good as to dance\nwith this fine lady, my brother?
What japery is this?! As you so clearly\nstated earlier, I am but an attendant,\nand not fit to dance with royalty.
And thus comes the EXCITEMENT!\nThe border of status, crossed for a single,\nsurreptitious night of dance and revels.
And if THIS doesn't bring a little levity to\nyour cold heart, I will admit my defeat.
...Or perhaps all your talk of being\nlevity-proof is nothing but wind?
I am in no such mood, and I will prove it.\nDance with me, {player_name}.
Er, we start out like this, right...?\nSorry. It's been a long time since\nI've had to dance formally.
Er, thanks, but you don't sound\ntoo pleased.

Because I went on a tirade about how
I could feel no levity, and yet levity is
beginning to encroach upon me as we
spin across this floor.
She led me like a lamb to slaughter.
Oh ho ho! And here I thought you weren't\nthe type of woman to become starry-eyed\nwith romance.
It seems I am the winner.\nIsn't that right, sylvan?

Ah, but dancing will not be the only
entertainment on offer this evening!
If everyone would be so kind as to
turn your gazes outside the window?
I told my brother I had invited another\nhonored guest—and that guest will now\nperform for our amusement!
Can you guess who it is?
Your Highness, look! There is a group\nof men outside battling fiends!
What is a horde this large doing\nin a wasteland such as this?
Captain! We should assume a defensive\nposition and hold our ground here!

No. Fighting a protracted battle when
reinforcements are not coming would
be dangerous. We'll find a weak point
in their ranks and break through.
But we came here at Her Highness Chelle's\ninvitation, did we not? Surely she will be\ndispatching reinforcements soon!
Her Highness is not that kind of person.\nWe must do this thing ourselves.
Understood, Captain! ...White Sparrows!\nDo honor to your name and FIGHT!
He was my teacher when I was still in\nthe capital. Much of what I am today\nis owed to him.
He's a master of the sword, but it won't\nmatter against numbers like that!
Eeeee hee hee! Such entertainment\ntruly befits my royal gala!
Everyone, clamber forth to the edge of\nyour seats and enjoy the show I have\nset out before you!
How can you do this to Leif, Sister?!\nHe was everything to us!
Which is what makes this so thrilling!
I pray you remember this naughty feeling\nas a taste of true adult fun.
Come on, everyone.\nLeif needs our help.
To arms, everyone! To arm...\nEr, Cleo? What are you doing?
W-wait a moment! I'm getting changed!
